casebody.data:
Richard JONES, Appellant,
v.
STATE of Missouri, Respondent. WD 80605 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Filed: December 18, 2018 Vincent K. Heitholt, Overland, Amicus Curiae; Damien S.B. Loyola, Kansas City for appellant. Shaun Mackelprang, Jefferson City for respondent. Before Division One: Lisa White Hardwick, Presiding Judge, Edward R. Ardini, Jr., and Thomas N. Chapman, Judges

ORDER

Per Curiam

Richard Jones appeals from the judgment denying his Rule 24.035 motion after he pled guilty to first-degree tampering with a motor vehicle and resisting arrest. Upon review of the briefs and the record, we find no error and affirm the judgment. We have provided the parties with a Memorandum explaining the reasons for our decision because a published opinion would have no precedential value.

AFFIRMED. Rule 84.16(b).
